    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="499"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/99.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to the Dominican
                            Republic</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed by the Minister for Foreign Affairs that he has instructed the
                    Dominican Minister at Washington,<note n="1" xml:id="d499fn1">Dr. Francisco J.
                        Peynado.</note> to consult with the Department in regard to the advisability
                    of an ultimatum from the Dominican to the Haitian Government, which is openly
                    violating treaties and international obligations. The Dominican Government
                    desires to know if we can help them in any way.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
